content:
IGeneratedTask Interface

Definition

An interface implemented by tasks that are generated by ITaskFactory instances.

In this Article

public interface IGeneratedTask : Microsoft.Build.Framework.ITask

Methods

GetPropertyValue(TaskPropertyInfo)

Gets the property value.

public object GetPropertyValue (Microsoft.Build.Framework.TaskPropertyInfo property);
Parameters
property
TaskPropertyInfo

The name of the property.

Returns
Object

The value of the named property.

Remarks

MSBuild calls this method after executing the task to get output parameters. All exceptions from this method will be caught in the taskExecution host and logged as a fatal task error.

SetPropertyValue(TaskPropertyInfo, Object)

Sets a property value.

public void SetPropertyValue (Microsoft.Build.Framework.TaskPropertyInfo property, object value);
Parameters
property
TaskPropertyInfo

The name of the property.

value
Object

The value to use.
